11.诚实说实话 善意的谎言

Some people believe that it is always important to tell the truth, while others think that telling white lies is sometimes necessary.
Discuss both views and give your own opinion.



is honest the best policy

white lie


Age-old question・・・昔からの質問







While honesty should generally be valued, I believe that telling a white lie can be justified when the truth would cause unnecessary harm and serve no constructive purpose.

Although honesty is generally regarded as a moral virtue, there are situations in which telling the truth may do more harm than good.

white lie：善意的谎言
brutal honesty：过于直白的诚实
spare someone’s feelings：顾及他人感受
do more harm than good：弊大于利
social lubricant：社交润滑剂（高级）
moral dilemma：道德困境

strain relationships
put a strain on a marriage
financial strain
emotional strain
put a strain on the system
Long working hours can strain family relationships.